      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WAIRARAPA (8) raced handy and did a good job to be beaten just three lengths after copping a check in the straight last start at Canterbury. Steps up from 1550m to 1850m today which looks a good option. Nicely placed to open her account. AUDACIOUSLY FRANK (2) produced a real eye-catcher last time out when at the races for only the second time, coming from next to last to be beaten a whisker over the mile at Kembla. Sure to be hard to hold out over a bit more ground. RESCHS MILK (7) has been safely held in her two runs to date, the latest at Canterbury over 1550m. Dam is by Savabeel so getting to a middle-distance trip might be the key. TITAN OF FURY (1) gave away a big start before launching late to be beaten under a length over 1600m at Taree recently. Nice effort two back when close up over 1890m here. Definite contender. ZORKO (5) is rock hard fit following a placing over 2200m at Scone last time. Must be considered.",
